  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The side and rear extension, as the first significant alteration to the building, would compromise the symmetry and uniformity of the design, and adversely affect the appearance of the building and streetscene. In addition, the side extension would reduce the gap between the building and adjacent substation to an unacceptable extent. Therefore the proposal would be contrary to policies D4 (Designing in context) and D11 (Alterations and extensions) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002, and fails to adhere to sections 2.4 and 2.5 of the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006), and Policies CS8 and CS9 of the Islington Core Strategy 2011."
